/-!
# Corrected physical scalar Program P-B closure

This aggregate head contains the concrete scalar physical-instantiation work of
Program P-B.

The preferred path now follows the actual analytic regularity hierarchy:

1. the covariant scalar wave residual is globalized across the total atlas;
2. the bulk `L²` adjunction defect is reduced to the global divergence integral;
3. the concrete value and normal Cauchy traces are realized in boundary `L²`;
4. spherical coarea gives the physical value-trace estimate unconditionally;
5. the local profiles `η(ν)` and `ν η(ν)` realize the exact value and normal
   Cauchy jets; a deck-invariant collar globalization and separate `H¹`/Euler
   estimates construct the graph-bounded smooth extension and the surjective
   completed trace;
6. the even shrinking profiles descend globally through the reflected-sphere
   deck action, vanish to first order at the throat, and converge strongly to
   the identity in physical bulk `L²`; consequently the zero-Cauchy minimal
   core is dense without an independent cutoff hypothesis;
7. Gårding and higher normal regularity construct the paired graph trace;
8. closed Dirichlet, Neumann and Robin Lagrangian domains follow;
9. smooth approximation of Hilbert adjoint pairs gives actual self-adjointness;
10. coercivity of one shifted form gives the reference resolvent and lower bound
    by Lax--Milgram;
11. compact approximations of `H¹ -> L²` give Rellich compactness;
12. the Fredholm alternative, finite multiplicity, spectral completeness and
    the lower spectral bound follow directly on the completed boundary triple.

The preferred endpoints are
`P0EFTJanusMappingTorusCanonicalPhysicalScalarCutoffClosedAnalyticClosure4D`
and the still more constructive
`P0EFTJanusMappingTorusCanonicalPhysicalScalarCauchyJetAnalyticClosure4D`.
They do not assume smooth bulk density, a collar-cutoff family, minimal-core
density, closability, domain density, completed trace surjectivity, shifted
surjectivity, semiboundedness or compact resolvent as independent inputs.
-/

